# Licence

This repository carries a **dual licence**, separating the engine from the
artwork. Both licences are reproduced verbatim under [`LICENSES/`](./LICENSES/).

---

## Code: European Union Public Licence v. 1.2 (EUPL-1.2)

Applies to all source code in the repository — the TypeScript under
`/app/src/` and `/app/scripts/`, the static visitor player and supporting
HTML/CSS/JavaScript under `/app/public/`, the GitHub Actions workflow under
`.github/workflows/`, and the manifests (`package.json`, `tsconfig.json`,
etc.).

- SPDX identifier: `EUPL-1.2`
- Full text: [`LICENSES/EUPL-1.2.txt`](./LICENSES/EUPL-1.2.txt)
- Canonical: <https://joinup.ec.europa.eu/collection/eupl/eupl-text-eupl-12>

The EUPL is the European-Union-recognised, GPL-compatible permissive copyleft
licence. Available in twenty-three official EU languages, all equally
authoritative — the Belgian-context choice for an open-source engine that may
be reused, modified, or redistributed.

## Creative content: Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-NoDerivatives 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-ND 4.0)

Applies to the literary work, the AI-voiced performance, and the printed
artefacts:

- The original short story — `story.md`, `story.html`, `God-Bless-USA.pdf`
- The director's score — `god-bless-usa_performance-script.md`,
  `god-bless-usa_performance-script.pdf`
- The rendered audio under `app/public/assets/audio/` (WAV, Opus, AAC), and
  the concatenated master `god-bless-usa.wav` / `.opus.ogg` / `.m4a`
- The print HTML files under `app/print/`
- The cover image `image.png`

You may share the work and credit the author. You may not use it commercially
or distribute modified versions. Commercial reuse — including by museums,
archives, or institutions seeking to redistribute beyond fair-use exhibition
— requires a separate written grant from the author.

- SPDX identifier: `CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0`
- Full text: [`LICENSES/CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0.txt`](./LICENSES/CC-BY-NC-ND-4.0.txt)
- Canonical: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0/>

This licence runs under **Belgian law** as governing jurisdiction.

